---
description: Comment intent rules for all languages in the repo
alwaysApply: true
---

# Comments explain intent, not mechanics

Comments explain intent, trade-offs, invariants, or non-obvious
platform behavior. Do not write comments that re-narrate what the
code literally says.

```python
# Wrong
# Increment the counter
counter += 1

# Right
# Bubbles without text still carry URIs we need for project inference,
# so we count them separately from message-carrying bubbles.
counter += 1
```

Same rule applies to JavaScript / JSX:

```jsx
// Wrong
// Set loading to true
setLoading(true);

// Right
// Reset the empty-state flash so the spinner is visible again while
// the refresh request is in flight.
setLoading(true);
```

# Rule drift

When a refactor materially changes a convention captured in any rule
under `.cursor/rules/`, update that rule in the same PR. Rules must
not drift from reality; a stale rule is worse than no rule.
